The 2970-ton vessel caught fire on Wednesday morning while berthed at one of the port's main quays.Several people in the city shared images of the vessel on social media including Ivan Sams on twitter. Looks like there's a ship on fire in Cape Town Harbour he tweeted.Looks like there's a ship on fire in Cape Town Harbour... pic.twitter.com/ZGxFoUeRsv Ivan Sams (@ivansams) November 2, 2016 Looks like there's a ship on fire in Cape Town Harbour... pic.twitter.com/ZGxFoUeRsvTransnet said crew members had been evacuated without injury. The immediate concern is to ensure no further injury loss of life or environmental pollution as the vessel is said to be carrying 150 kl of fuel and 800 000 pieces of plastic packaging material said a statement by Transnet. Heavy smoke billowed from the vessel over the city centre.Port fire-fighting teams were working closely with the City of Cape Town s fire and emergency services to control the fire the cause of which is yet to be established. - TMG Digital/The Times